(2355, 106, 'story-en', 'In the XVIII century Catherine II went on a long journey to Latvia, which is famous for its unspoilt nature, where Catherine the great was acquainted with a unique natural miracle – Elier . The ancient inhabitants of the Baltic States in order to maintain their beauty and longevity used Elier – dirt that lies deep at the bottom of an ancient lake. Nowadays, this place became a reserve and Deposit Elier. Grand Empress enjoyed the power of this treasure and called it the elixir of beauty and youth. Elier was one of the mysteries of her femininity, attractiveness and beauty. Throughout his life, the Empress used Elier bath to maintain health and youth, in order to captivate and conquer the beauty of young fans.\r\n\r\nIn 1785 Catherine the Great gave his blessing and allowed the use of Elier in folk medicine, as it was entitled to use only members of the Imperial family.\r\n\r\nElier (in the language of the ancient Balts "ellõ liegã era" – the healing mud of an ancient lake) – is the world''s only VYSOKOORGANIZOVANNAJA the curative mud, which was formed in karst caves, more than 10 million years ago, it is a complex of natural organic components. Unique organic mud was successfully used in skin rejuvenation procedures for more than 200 years, and in our time have been studied leading biochemists around the world and is clinically tested.'),
